---
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import ImageModal from '../../components/ImageModal.astro';
import ClickableImage from '../../components/ClickableImage.astro';
export const prerender = true;
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/favicon.png" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
    <title>Baby Name Blossoms - Annie Liao</title>
  </head>
  <body class="bg-gray-50">
    <Header />

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <main class="pt-20">
      <!-- Hero Section -->
      <section class="py-32 px-6 bg-white">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
          <div class="mb-6">
            <span class="text-6xl md:text-8xl font-light text-gray-500">04</span>
          </div>
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-light text-gray-900 mb-6">
            Baby Name Blossoms
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-light text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
            When art meets data: My first D3.js adventure that transforms decades of baby name trends into flowers, one petal at a time.
          </p>

          <!-- Visual Tags -->
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 items-center mb-8">
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-600">React</span>
            <span class="text-gray-400">‚Ä¢</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-600">D3.js</span>
            <span class="text-gray-400">‚Ä¢</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-600">Data Viz</span>
            <span class="text-gray-400">‚Ä¢</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-600">Personal</span>
          </div>

          <!-- Quick Links -->
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
            <a href="https://baby-name-blossoms.netlify.app/" target="_blank" 
               class="inline-block px-4 py-2 bg-gray-100 text-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-200 rounded-md font-medium transition-colors duration-200">
              Live Demo
            </a>
            <a href="https://github.com/liaowow/baby-names" target="_blank" 
               class="inline-block px-4 py-2 bg-gray-100 text-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-200 rounded-md font-medium transition-colors duration-200">
              GitHub
            </a>
            <a href="https://dev.to/liaowow/when-art-meets-data-flowers-as-visual-metaphor-1ekl" target="_blank" 
               class="inline-block px-4 py-2 bg-gray-100 text-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-200 rounded-md font-medium transition-colors duration-200">
              Blog Post
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Project Details -->
      <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-gray-50">
        <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
          
          <!-- The Spark -->
          <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-16">
            <p class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-light text-gray-900 leading-relaxed mb-8">
              Fresh out of coding bootcamp, I stumbled across something magical called Film Flowers.
            </p>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
              It was an art piece that turned movie data into beautiful, blooming visualizations. As I scrolled through the delicate petals representing different films, a question sparked:
            </p>
            <p class="text-xl font-medium text-gray-900 italic border-l-4 border-gray-300 pl-6">
              "What if baby names could bloom too?"
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- The Journey -->
          <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-light text-gray-900 mb-8">A week of discovery</h2>
            <div class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-none">
              <p class="mb-4">
                That simple question launched my first real D3.js adventure. I had no idea what I was doing, but I had 100 years of baby name data from the Social Security Administration and a head full of ideas.
              </p>
              <p class="mb-4">
                The concept was beautiful in its simplicity: let each name become a flower. More popular names would get more petals, like how flowers in perfect conditions bloom bigger and more vibrant. But how could I make each flower unique?
              </p>
              <p class="mb-4">
                Then it hit me: the vowels. Emma would get colors for E and A. Oliver would bloom with O, I, and E hues. Suddenly, every name had its own personality, its own visual signature.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- The Magic Moment -->
          <div class="mb-16">
            <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-center">
                <div>
                  <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-gray-900 mb-4">Before: Just structure</h3>
                  <ClickableImage 
                    src="/images/baby_name_blossoms_plain.png" 
                    alt="Baby Name Blossoms flowers before vowel coloring"
                    modalId="blossomModal"
                    class="w-full h-auto rounded-lg"
                  />
                </div>
                <div>
                  <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-gray-900 mb-4">After: Pure magic ‚ú®</h3>
                  <ClickableImage 
                    src="/images/baby_name_blossoms_color.png" 
                    alt="Baby Name Blossoms flowers with vowel coloring"
                    modalId="blossomModal"
                    class="w-full h-auto rounded-lg"
                  />
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="text-center text-gray-600 mt-6">
                When the vowel colors first painted across those flowers, I knew I'd created something special.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Behind the Scenes -->
          <div class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-light text-gray-900 mb-6">What I learned (the hard way)</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                <span class="text-2xl">üòÖ</span>
                <div>
                  <p class="font-medium text-gray-900">D3.js doesn't play nice with React</p>
                  <p class="text-gray-600">Spent way too long fighting the framework instead of working with it.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                <span class="text-2xl">üé®</span>
                <div>
                  <p class="font-medium text-gray-900">SVG has its own mysterious ways</p>
                  <p class="text-gray-600">Positioning elements felt like solving puzzles in a foreign language.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                <span class="text-2xl">üí°</span>
                <div>
                  <p class="font-medium text-gray-900">Simple solutions often work best</p>
                  <p class="text-gray-600">The vowel-color idea was elegantly simple, and that's what made it work.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                <span class="text-2xl">‚ú®</span>
                <div>
                  <p class="font-medium text-gray-900">Data + creativity = pure magic</p>
                  <p class="text-gray-600">When numbers become art, something beautiful happens.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- The Tech Stack -->
          <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-gray-200 mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-gray-900 mb-6">Built with</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-6 text-center">
              <div>
                <div class="text-2xl mb-2">‚öõÔ∏è</div>
                <p class="font-medium text-gray-900">React</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Component structure</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="text-2xl mb-2">üìä</div>
                <p class="font-medium text-gray-900">D3.js</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">First time using it!</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="text-2xl mb-2">üìà</div>
                <p class="font-medium text-gray-900">SSA Data</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">100 years of names</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="text-2xl mb-2">üöÄ</div>
                <p class="font-medium text-gray-900">Netlify</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Live deployment</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Try It Yourself -->
          <div class="text-center">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-light text-gray-900 mb-4">Ready to see the garden?</h2>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">
              Explore 100 years of American baby names, each one blooming with its own story.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
              <a href="https://baby-name-blossoms.netlify.app/" target="_blank" 
                 class="inline-block px-6 py-3 bg-gray-100 text-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-200 rounded-md font-medium transition-colors duration-200">
                üå∏ View the Garden
              </a>
              <a href="https://github.com/liaowow/baby-names" target="_blank" 
                 class="inline-block px-6 py-3 bg-gray-100 text-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-200 rounded-md font-medium transition-colors duration-200">
                View Code
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>


        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Back Navigation -->
      <section class="py-12 px-6 bg-gray-50 border-t border-gray-200">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
          <a
            href="/#work"
            class="inline-block px-4 py-2 bg-gray-900 text-white hover:bg-gray-700 rounded-md font-medium transition-colors duration-200"
          >
            Back to All Projects
          </a>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mt-2">
            Explore more case studies and technical projects
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <ImageModal id="blossomModal" />
  </body>
</html>